author: rhuijben
msg: Ensure that adds and deletes are reported in the right order in the
--notice-ancestry mode of the repos-wc diff editor.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/diff_editor.c
(dir_baton_t): Add local status cache. Redefine compared.
(ensure_local_info): New function.
(walk_local_nodes_diff): Handle pre-compared functions more
reliable.
(ensure_local_only_handled): New function.
(delete_entry): Redefine as user of ensure_local_only_handled.
(add_directory): Make sure a local delete is handled before a remote
add.
(open_directory): Make sure local deletes are reported before remote
edits, which will be reported as adds.
(add_file): Make sure remote deletes are added before local adds.
(open_file): Make sure local deletes are reported before remote
edits, which will be reported as adds.
(close_file): Report local file changes directly after remote changes.
* subversion/tests/cmdline/diff_tests.py
(simple_ancestry): New function.
(test_list): Add simple_ancestry.
